{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/pancreatitis-chronic/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"2a28979a-edfb-5704-92b2-7fdaf8a8913f","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 38e5700e-7b40-4878-a61a-a7f201880045 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 38e5700e-7b40-4878-a61a-a7f201880045 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 40674962-8fdd-4427-b959-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field 793dcfc3-8bba-44b6-9ecc-a7f201880045 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 793dcfc3-8bba-44b6-9ecc-a7f201880045 --><!-- begin field ec50b7b4-8bc0-45c1-b28f-a7f201880045 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field ec50b7b4-8bc0-45c1-b28f-a7f201880045 --><!-- begin field e83818b8-a0fe-422e-8b50-a7f201880045 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field e83818b8-a0fe-422e-8b50-a7f201880045 --><!-- begin field 23756ac0-f3ae-4172-a1c9-a7f201880045 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 23756ac0-f3ae-4172-a1c9-a7f201880045 --><!-- begin field d2059e3d-7988-4c0b-b75e-a7f201880045 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field d2059e3d-7988-4c0b-b75e-a7f201880045 --><!-- begin field 163696f2-e5e1-49dd-9dee-a7f201880045 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 163696f2-e5e1-49dd-9dee-a7f201880045 --><!-- end item 40674962-8fdd-4427-b959-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"d3bdd09e-867d-5b95-ba2d-6665c70e40a5","topicId":"d9dbbfb6-e615-4d8a-8af3-3c73ae8f1e4e","topicName":"Pancreatitis - chronic","slug":"pancreatitis-chronic","lastRevised":"Last revised in June 2016","chapters":[{"id":"bfa52d50-3b9c-54bf-b86b-a6ec4d6efd15","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"cb0ed96c-bed5-5834-b1fc-c621b24d0be4","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"a99366ef-8502-55e8-b57b-f9b0fcd42a4d","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"5aece8a2-4765-5931-ba08-0c279235f4b9","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"22a72223-9da2-5684-960b-6a02559bd517","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"0f0b49d0-3b8f-52bf-8038-0c47eb6e82dd","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"431788bd-8b44-5c4c-a97b-656fe3edf51c","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"6929fb38-356f-5b82-a484-b1138878a6a7","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"8f68d6c6-b43e-5ef7-aa86-ab44f8dfd1a4","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItem